President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. Sean O'Donnell of Maryland is nominated to be the Inspector General of the Environmental Protection Agency. O'Donnell has extensive experience in criminal and civil matters, working with multiple inspector general offices. John "Jack" Bobbitt of Texas is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Housing and Urban Development. He currently serves as the Deputy Assistant Secretary for Housing Operations at the Department of Housing and Urban Development. Laurie Todd-Smith of Mississippi is appointed to be the Director of the Women's Bureau, Department of Labor. She has a background in education policy and workforce development. Additionally, President Trump announced the intent to appoint several individuals to serve on the National Infrastructure Advisory Council and the National Cancer Advisory Board.